\f0\fs51\fsmilli25995 \cf2 1 | Introduction to Medicine and\
Healthcare
\fs21\fsmilli10995 In this lesson, students are introduced to the field of medicine and healthcare. We explain what\
healthcare professionals (doctors, nurses, and other specialists) do, and how hospitals and\
clinics help people stay healthy. For example, we might describe how a pediatrician cares for\
children or how surgeons and nurses work together during an operation. The lesson shows that\
medicine combines science and compassion, and that many different people (doctors, nurses,\
pharmacists, technicians) work together on a medical team.\
After this lesson, students will understand the role of healthcare workers and the basics of a\
hospital or clinic. They will know why doctors study science and how medical teams use\
knowledge of the body to treat and prevent illness.
