\fs51\fsmilli25995 2 | Cells, DNA, and Heredity
\fs21\fsmilli10995 In this lesson, students learn about cells and the genetic material inside them. We explain that\
every living thing is made of cells, and that each cell contains DNA; the instructions for how the\
body works. We describe how DNA is organized into genes and chromosomes, which determine\
traits (like eye color or blood type) inherited from parents. For example, if one parent has brown\
eyes and the other blue, children may inherit one of those genes. We also introduce the idea\
that changes (mutations) in DNA can cause genetic diseases (like sickle cell anemia or cystic\
fibrosis).\
After this lesson, students will know that DNA is a blueprint inside cells and that genes are\
inherited from parents. They will understand that our cells follow genetic instructions to grow\
and function, and that some diseases happen when genes don\'92t work correctly.
