\f1\b \cf2 Cells Have DNA: 
\f0\b0 Each cell in the body contains DNA, the molecule that stores genetic\
information. DNA looks like a twisted ladder (double helix) and is found in the cell\'92s\
nucleus.\

\f1\b Genes and Chromosomes: 
\f0\b0 DNA is organized into genes (units of heredity). Humans\
have 23 pairs of chromosomes carrying thousands of genes. We get one set of\
chromosomes from our mother and one from our father.\

\f1\b Inheritance: 
\f0\b0 Genes carry traits. For example, if the\
\'93brown eye\'94 gene is dominant, a\
