\fs51\fsmilli25995 3 | Blood and Immunity
\fs21\fsmilli10995 In this lesson, students explore the composition of blood and the basics of the immune system.\
We explain that blood is a liquid tissue containing red blood cells (which carry oxygen), white\
blood cells (which fight infections), platelets (which help blood clot), and plasma (the liquid). For\
example, red blood cells pick up oxygen from the lungs and deliver it to cells, while white blood\
cells act like guards that attack germs. We also introduce the immune system: the body\'92s\
defense against invaders. This includes antibodies and special white blood cells that recognize\
and remember germs. We mention how vaccines train the immune system to recognize specific\
viruses or bacteria.\
After this lesson, students will know the main parts of blood and their roles. They will understand\
that red cells carry oxygen, white cells fight infections, and platelets stop bleeding by clotting.\
They will also understand that the immune system protects us from disease.
