\f1\b \cf2 Blood Components: 
\f0\b0 Blood is about 55% plasma (liquid) and 45% cells. Red blood cells\
contain hemoglobin to carry oxygen. White blood cells include many types (like\
lymphocytes and neutrophils) that identify and destroy germs. Platelets are tiny\
fragments that gather at wounds to form clots and stop bleeding.\

\f1\b Oxygen Transport: 
\f0\b0 Red cells pick up oxygen in the lungs and deliver it to every cell.\
They also carry carbon dioxide (a waste gas) back to the lungs to be exhaled.\

\f1\b Immune Defense: 
\f0\b0 White blood cells protect the body from infection. When germs enter,\
the immune system responds with inflammation (fever, swelling) to fight them. Vaccines\
introduce a safe piece of a germ so the immune system can prepare defenses\
(antibodies) without getting sick.\

