\fs51\fsmilli25995 4 | The Heart and Circulatory Health
\fs21\fsmilli10995 In this lesson, students study the heart in detail and learn how it works as a pump. We describe\
that the heart has four chambers (two atria and two ventricles) and valves that control blood\
flow. We explain how blood enters the heart from the body (right side), goes to the lungs for\
oxygen, then returns to the heart (left side) and is pumped to the rest of the body. We also\
introduce blood pressure (the force of blood on vessel walls) and why too high pressure can\
damage vessels. We mention how a clogged artery can lead to a heart attack.\
After this lesson, students will understand that the heart is a muscular pump with valves that\
keep blood moving one way. They will know that blood goes through a loop: body \uc0\u8594  heart \u8594 \
lungs \uc0\u8594  heart \u8594  body. They will also learn that high blood pressure and unhealthy habits can\
strain the heart.
