\f1\b \cf2 Heart Structure: 
\f0\b0 The heart has four chambers: two atria on top and two ventricles on\
bottom. Valves between them open and close with each heartbeat to prevent backflow.\

\f1\b Blood Flow: 
\f0\b0 Blood with low oxygen enters the right side of the heart and is pumped to\
the lungs to pick up oxygen. Oxygen-rich blood returns to the left side, then is pumped\
out to all body tissues.\

\f1\b Blood Pressure: 
\f0\b0 Blood pressure is the push of blood on artery walls. It has two\
numbers (systolic/diastolic). High blood pressure (\'93hypertension\'94) can strain the heart\
and harm vessels, increasing risk of heart attack or stroke.\

