\f1\b \cf2 Macronutrients: 
\f0\b0 Carbohydrates (sugars and starches) are the body\'92s quick energy\
source; proteins are used to build muscles, enzymes, and repair tissues; fats provide\
long-term energy and help absorb certain vitamins. Each gram of carbohydrate or\
protein provides 4 calories, fat provides 9 calories.\

\f1\b Vitamins and Minerals: 
\f0\b0 Vitamins (like C, D) and minerals (like calcium, iron) do not give\
energy but are essential for health. For example, vitamin C helps heal wounds, calcium\
builds strong bones, and iron helps red blood cells carry oxygen.\

\f1\b Balanced Diet: 
\f0\b0 A healthy diet has all nutrients: grains (carbs), proteins (meat, beans),\
fats (oils, nuts in moderation), and plenty of fruits and vegetables. Too much junk food\
(sugar/fat) can lead to obesity and other issues (like diabetes or high cholesterol).\

