\f0\b0 Insulin (from the pancreas) tells body cells to take in glucose from the\
blood to use for energy. When insulin is missing or ineffective, glucose builds up in the\
blood instead of entering cells.\

\f1\b Type 1 vs Type 2: 
\f0\b0 Type 1 diabetes usually starts in childhood \'96 the immune system\
