\fs51\fsmilli25995 13 | Heart Disease and Lifestyle
\fs21\fsmilli10995 In this lesson, students learn about heart disease and how lifestyle affects the circulatory\
system. We explain that coronary heart disease happens when arteries to the heart muscle\
become narrowed by fatty deposits (cholesterol plaques). Over time, this can reduce blood flow,\
causing chest pain (angina) or a heart attack (when blood supply is suddenly cut off). We\
discuss risk factors: unhealthy diet (high in saturated fats), lack of exercise, smoking (which\
damages vessels), and high blood pressure. For example, diets high in fried foods can increase\
\'93bad\'94 cholesterol, clogging arteries. We stress prevention: a balanced diet, regular exercise, and\
not smoking keep the heart and vessels healthy.\
After this lesson, students will understand that heart disease is often caused by blocked\
arteries, and that many risk factors are controllable. They will know why eating fruits and\
vegetables, exercising, and avoiding smoking help keep the heart strong.
