\f1\b \cf2 Asthma: 
\f0\b0 During an asthma attack, the muscles around bronchial tubes tighten and\
lining swells, reducing airflow. Symptoms: wheezing (a whistling sound), shortness of\
breath, chest tightness, cough. Asthma inhalers usually contain bronchodilators (to open\
