\f1\b \cf2 Balanced Diet: 
\f0\b0 Eating a variety of foods gives essential nutrients. Whole grains, fruits,\
and vegetables provide fiber and vitamins; protein foods help build tissue. Limiting sugar\
and junk food prevents obesity and related diseases. Drinking plenty of water helps\
kidneys and brain function.\

\f1\b Regular Exercise: 
\f0\b0 Physical activity (like walking, biking, sports) keeps muscles strong,\
burns excess fat, and helps the heart and lungs work efficiently. Exercise releases\
endorphins, chemicals in the brain that improve mood.\

\f1\b Hygiene and Safety: 
\f0\b0 Simple habits prevent illness: washing hands removes germs;\
brushing teeth prevents cavities and gum disease; cooking meat thoroughly kills\
bacteria. Safety measures (seatbelts, helmets) prevent injuries.\

