\fs21\fsmilli10995 In this lesson, students learn about common medical tools and diagnostic tests. We explain that\
doctors use various instruments and technologies to check health and diagnose problems\
without guessing. For example, a stethoscope is used to listen to heartbeats and lung sounds. A\
thermometer measures body temperature to detect fever. We describe blood tests: a small\
blood sample can be analyzed for sugar level, infection markers, or blood cell counts. For\
imaging, we review that X-rays let doctors see bones (and check for fractures), MRI/CT scans\
show detailed images of organs, and ultrasounds use sound waves to view internal organs or\
babies during pregnancy. We emphasize how these tools help doctors make accurate\
diagnoses.\
After this lesson, students will know several medical tools and what they do. They will\
understand that these tools help detect health issues early (like catching pneumonia on an\
X-ray or anemia via blood test). They will also learn that technology in medicine is always\
improving (for example, wearable devices can monitor heart rate at home).
