\f1\b Laboratory Tests: 
\f0\b0 A small vial of blood can tell a lot (glucose level, white blood cell\
count for infection, cholesterol). Urine tests check kidney function and detect sugar or\
proteins.\

\f1\b Imaging: 
\f0\b0 X-rays pass through the body to create images of bones (white on film). MRI\
(using magnets) and CT (X-ray cross-sections) create detailed pictures of soft tissues\
(brain, organs). Ultrasound (sound waves) images are used for viewing the heart and\
growing fetus. These help doctors see inside without surgery.\

