\f1\b \cf2 Bleeding: 
\f0\b0 For bleeding wounds, apply firm pressure with a clean cloth or bandage to\
stop bleeding. Raise the injured part if possible. If bleeding is severe or doesn\'92t stop,\
seek medical help.\

\f1\b Burns: 
\f0\b0 Cool a burn under running cool (not ice) water for several minutes. Cover with a\
clean non-sticky dressing. Do not apply toothpaste or oils. Severe burns require\
emergency care.\

\f1\b Choking: 
\f0\b0 If someone can\'92t speak or cough, they are choking. For a child/teen, perform\
back blows (stand behind, bend forward, and give 5 sharp blows between the shoulder\
blades). If that fails, do abdominal thrusts (Heimlich maneuver) if trained. Always tell an\
adult or call 911 if someone is choking and cannot breathe.\

\f1\b CPR (Basic): 
\f0\b0 If someone is unresponsive and not breathing normally, begin CPR: give\
30 chest compressions (pushing hard and fast in the center of the chest) and 2 rescue\
breaths (cover mouth and blow air into their lungs) if trained. Continue until help arrives.\

